      <did>
         <head id="a1">DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY</head>
         <unittitle encodinganalog="MARC 245" label="Title:">Gustav Jaeger Requardt papers, </unittitle><unitdate encodinganalog="MARC 245" type="inclusive">1905-1966.</unitdate>
         <unitid label="Collection Number:">2548</unitid>
         <origination label="Creator:"> 
		  
            <persname encodinganalog="100" normal="Requardt, Gustave Jaeger, 1886-1978.">Gustav Jaeger Requardt, 1886-1978.</persname>
		
         </origination>
         <physdesc encodinganalog="MARC 300" label="Quantity:"><extent>1.8 cubic feet</extent></physdesc>
         <physdesc label="Forms of Material:">Correspondence, diary, reports, certificates, clippings, photographs, press releases.</physdesc>
         <repository label="Repository:"> Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library</repository>
         <abstract label="Abstract:">Printed and photocopied items, mainly concerning Requardt's student years at Cornell University, his participation in alumni activities, his career in sanitary engineering, and his
		  interest in national politics and public affairs. </abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Engineer.</p>
         <p>Cornell University Class of 1909.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence; diary (1962) of Requardt's tour of Scandinavia, Holland, and West Germeny; reports; certificates; clippings; photographs; press releases; biographical sketches on the Requardt family; and printed and photocopied items, mainly concerning Requardt's student years at
		  Cornell University, his participation in alumni activities, his career in sanitary engineering, and his interest in national politics and public affairs. Includes material relating to his partnership in Whitman, Requardt, and Associates (Baltimore, Maryland). Chief correspondents include John Marshall Butler, George H. Fallon, and
		  Herbert R. O'Conor.</p>
      </scopecontent>
